  "confidence": "HIGH",
  "coaching_summary": "This routine demonstrates a foundational understanding of the required skills for JO Level 6 Uneven Bars, but the execution is severely hampered by consistent and significant form breaks. The most critical and recurring issue is the inability to cast to horizontal, which incurs a substantial penalty for every attempt. Additionally, general body tension, particularly in the knees and toes, is lacking throughout the routine, leading to numerous micro-deductions that compound quickly. The dismount showed an early tuck, indicating a timing issue in flight. While the gymnast successfully completed all elements, the quality of execution needs drastic improvement to be competitive.",
  "top_3_fixes": [
    "Mastering the Cast to Handstand Shape: Focus on drills that emphasize a strong hollow-body shape, active shoulders, and a powerful 'toe beat' to drive the hips over the bar, ensuring casts consistently reach or exceed horizontal. Utilize spotting and resistance bands to build strength in the correct positions.",
    "Developing Full Body Tension: Implement conditioning drills specifically targeting core strength, locked knees (KTM), and pointed toes (TPM) in every position. Practice holding perfect hollow and arch shapes, and integrate these shapes into every swing and skill to eliminate bent knees, flexed feet, and piked hips.",
    "Improving Dismount Timing and Shape: Work on dismount drills that focus on achieving maximum height and a stretched, open body position *before* initiating the tuck. Use a trampoline or tumble track for repetition, emphasizing a strong block off the bar and delaying the tuck until the apex of flight to improve rotation and landing control."
  ],
